<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="public-adj">public <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pʌblɪk/    美 /'pʌblɪk/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 大众的；公众的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a danger to public health
对大众健康的危害</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The media has a powerful influence on public opinion.
媒体对公众舆论有很大的影响力。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[只用于名词前]公立的；公务的；公共的</strong></h4>
<p>反 private： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a public library / school
公立图书馆 / 学校</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a public official / servant
公务员</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>public transport / transportation</strong>
公共交通(工具)</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>“No Smoking” signs will be put up in the public places.
“禁止吸烟”的标识将会张贴在公共场所。</p><footer>2010 广东</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>公开的；众所周知的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Being a <strong>public figure</strong> today is a lot more difficult than it used to be.
如今，做一名公众人物要比过去难多了。</p><footer>2013 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Some of the world’s heaviest pumpkins were on <strong>public display</strong> in New York for a few days.
一些世界上最重的南瓜在纽约公开展出了几天。</p><footer>2012 浙江改</footer></div></div>